href="gr-000G.xml"
addr="gr-000G"
title="Group">Group</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  G]]></fr:tex> be an element, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subset. We say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Centralizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[ab=ba]]></fr:tex>. In other words, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  C_{G}(B)]]></fr:tex> is an element of the <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-001O.xml"
addr="gr-001O"
title="Centralizer of a subset">centralizer</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be subsets. We say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Centralizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if every element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> centralizes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>; i.e., <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq  C_{G}(B)]]></fr:tex> is a subset of the centralizer of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq  G]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-001B.xml"
addr="gr-001B"
title="Subgroup">Subgroup</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subset. We say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Centralizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if every <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h\in  H]]></fr:tex> centralizes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>. In other words, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq  C_{G}(B)]]></fr:tex> is a subgroup of the centralizer of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol><fr:p>In the preceding three definitions, we may replace <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> with a subgroup <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K\leq  G]]></fr:tex> or an element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  G]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
