title="Group">Group</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  G]]></fr:tex> be an element. We say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Normalizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a^{-1}Ba=B]]></fr:tex>; in other words <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  N_{G}(B)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>. We say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Normalizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if every element of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> normalizes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subgroup of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>. We say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Normalizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if every element of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> normalizes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol><fr:p>We can replace <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> with a subgroup <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K\leq  G]]></fr:tex> and the definition of "normalizes" generalizes accordingly; and we can replace <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> with an element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>, and the definition "normalizes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>" is just a synonym for "normalizes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{b\}]]></fr:tex>".</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>